All Classes

Class Summary 
Class Description
Block
An object containing all the information about a block required by the game.
BlockLibrary
An object that manages all the blocks in particular world.
Chaos
This is just a way to get all the existing blocks into the world.
ConsoleConnector
Console connector is the sole broker between the Message queues and the network.
FileConstants  
Generator
Contains generators that create new terrain.
ImageWorld
Creates a top-down image of the world.
Layers
A more complicated generator that takes multiple layers and stack them on top of each other.
Main
Yikes, what a mess of a file.
Simplex
A basic terrain where the height is taken from a 2D Simplex.
Sine
A basic terrain where the x height is generated by the sine function, and the z height is generated by the tangent function.
Space
Functions for converting world coordinates to Volume coordinates and vice-versa.
Volume
A unit of blocks in three dimensions that has a height, width and depth.
World
A collection of Volumes and their relations to each other, to allow for dynamic generation of the world in small pieces at a time.
